<title>USA: Patterson Energy Inc Q1 net falls.</title>
<headline>Patterson Energy Inc Q1 net falls.</headline>
<dateline>SNYDER, Texas 1997-04-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>THREE MONTHS ENDED MARCH 31</p>
<p>						     1997	    1996</p>
<p>Revenues</p>
<p>  Drilling				 $27,564,000   $14,096,000</p>
<p>  Oil and Gas Sales			2,633,000     1,690,000</p>
<p>  Other					  444,000	 460,000</p>
<p> Total Revenues			   30,641,000    16,246,000</p>
<p> Operating Income			  2,640,000	 244,000</p>
<p> Net Income				  1,640,000     2,487,000</p>
<p>Net Income per Share</p>
<p>  Primary					   0.25	    0.51</p>
<p>  Assuming full dilution			0.25	    0.51</p>
<p>Average Shares Outstanding</p>
<p>  Primary				    6,604,000     4,877,000</p>
<p>  Assuming full dilution		 6,604,000     4,883,000</p>
<p>NOTE: 1996 Q1 includes net deferred income tax benefit of $2,402,000 or $0.49 per fully diluted share.</p>
<p>Q1 1996 restated to reflect the July 1996 merger with Tucker Drilling Co Inc under pooling of interests accounting method.</p>
<p>There were 6,604,000 fully diluted shares outstanding during Q1 1997 compared to 4,883,000 fully diluted shares outstanding a year ago.  This 35 percent increase in outstanding shares reflects successful IPO of 1,763,000 Patterson common shares in January 1997.</p>
<p>In February, the company's underwriters exercised their overallotment option to purchase an additional 300,000 shares. At March 31, 1997, there were 7,071,000 shares outstanding.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610</p>
</text>
